      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Capitalization</strong> - All codes are recorded in lowercase alphabetic characters.
      </div>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Order of codes</strong> - When a <strong>continuing resource</strong> which is authenticated by an ISSN Center
                     moves its place of publication to another country, responsibility for ISSN Network data
                     elements is assumed by the ISSN Network center in the new country of publication. The
                     authentication code for the current authenticating agency is added to field 042.
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>042</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>nlc<strong>$a</strong>isds/c<strong>$a</strong>nsdp
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div><br><br>LC, NSDP, LAC, ISSN Canada, or the ISSN UK Centre may consider the item to be a
                     continuing resource, while one of the others may not. Consequently, the field could
                     contain one code beginning with an "x" and one code not beginning with an "x."
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
